Health authorities say the infections may have been caused by water from a contaminated borehole in the city&#8217;s Mbare suburb. JOHANNESBURG A child has died and dozens have fallen ill in Zimbabwe from a suspected typhoid outbreak in the capital Harare.Health authorities say the infections may have been caused by water from a contaminated borehole in the city s Mbare suburb.Thirteen-year-old Ivy Makwara died on Christmas day.The state-run Herald says she had been taken to the Beatrice Road Infectious Diseases Hospital after she fell ill.Nine other residents from Mbare suburb are in hospital and health officials fear they too may have typhoid. Thirty others have already been treated and discharged.Early this year one person died and hundreds got sick in Harare from typhoid that spread as water shortages worsened.